          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-03-18T14:35:17Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Railroad Safety and Positive Train Control Extension Act</b></p> <p> Revises the railroad safety risk reduction program.</p> <p>Extends from December 31, 2015, to December 31, 2020, the deadline for submission to the Secretary of Transportation by each Class I railroad carrier and each entity providing regularly scheduled intercity or commuter rail passenger transportation of a plan for implementing a positive train control (PTC) system on certain of its tracks.</p> <p>Authorizes the Secretary to extend the implementation deadline, upon application, in one-year increments, if specified circumstances exist. </p> <p>Directs the Secretary to revise federal regulations requiring a Class II or III railroad (including a tourist or excursion railroad) to equip its locomotives with an onboard PTC system to operate in PTC territory.</p> <p>Extends for five years the time for such railroad to meet the deadline for equipping its locomotives with a PTC system.</p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
        <item>
          <actionDesc>Reported to Senate with amendment(s)</actionDesc>
          <updateDate>2016-09-22T13:05:24Z</updateDate>
          <actionDate>2016-09-22</actionDate>
          <versionCode>01</versionCode>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-03-09T19:40:05Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Railroad Safety and Positive Train Control Extension Act</b></p> <p> (Sec. 2) This bill revises the railroad safety risk reduction program.</p> <p>The bill extends from December 31, 2015, to December 31, 2020, the deadline for submission to the Department of Transportation (DOT) by each Class I railroad carrier and each entity providing regularly scheduled intercity or commuter rail passenger transportation of a plan for implementing a positive train control (PTC) system on certain of its tracks.</p> <p>(Sec. 3) DOT may extend the implementation deadline, upon application, in one-year increments, if specified circumstances exist. </p> <p>(Sec. 4) The bill directs DOT to revise federal regulations requiring a Class II or III railroad (including a tourist or excursion railroad) to extend by five years the deadlines for equipping its locomotives with an onboard PTC system to operate in PTC territory and applicable reporting requirements.</p>  <p>(Sec. 5) The bill requires Class I railroad carriers and each entity providing regularly scheduled intercity or commuter rail passenger transportation to submit annual progress reports to DOT on the status of plans to implement a PTC system. </p>]]></text>
          <name>Reported to Senate with amendment(s)</name>
        </item>
